mariadb cheat sheet for fedora:

start mariadb:
> systemctl start mariadb.service ## use restart after update

enable autostart on boot:
> systemctl enable mariadb.service

connect to MySQL database (localhost) with pasword
>mysql -u root -p
OR
>mysql -h localhost -u root -p

for more see:
http://www.if-not-true-then-false.com/2013/install-mariadb-on-fedora-centos-rhel/
